<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40081a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40081a">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40081a"> 81(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> mother&apos;s son</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&hellip; the scandalous and absurd legend which explained the names of the children of Lot by Phein&eacute; and Thamma as &ldquo;Moab&rdquo; (Mu-ab) the water or semen of the father, and &ldquo;Ammon&rdquo; as mother&apos;s son, that is, bastard. <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 228</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
